  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3460094953" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3460094953" />
    <a title="Tom Stamper" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24682440-tom-stamper"><img alt="Tom Stamper" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1471402186p2/24682440.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3460094953?book_show_action=true">Jul 24, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tom Stamper" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tom Stamper" href="/user/show/24682440-tom-stamper">Tom Stamper</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24682440-tom-stamper?shelf=american-history">american-history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24682440-tom-stamper?shelf=history">history</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3460094953" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8978623549243988764">Blood and Thunder could easily be called Kit Carson’s adventures in New Mexico as he is the primary character and New Mexico the primary location. There is some info here on John C. Fremont, James K Polk, and senator Thomas Hart Benton, but they all feel like tangential threads of the Carson story. <br/><br/>The essence of the story is that Kit Carson lived up to his reputation unlike many other western folk heroes. The plot is more or less Carson&apos;s encounters with the Navajo Indians and Spanish colonists</span>
  <span id="freeText8978623549243988764" style="display:none">Blood and Thunder could easily be called Kit Carson’s adventures in New Mexico as he is the primary character and New Mexico the primary location. There is some info here on John C. Fremont, James K Polk, and senator Thomas Hart Benton, but they all feel like tangential threads of the Carson story. <br /><br />The essence of the story is that Kit Carson lived up to his reputation unlike many other western folk heroes. The plot is more or less Carson's encounters with the Navajo Indians and Spanish colonists that would soon be supplanted by the United States. I found it flowed easily enough but it was more info about Kit Carson than I needed, while I would have liked more on Zachery Taylor or Winfield Scott and those heroes of the Mexican War who would figure prominently in the Civil War. <br /><br />Kit Carson never learned to read and could eventually write his own name so it’s funny when his men tricked him into signing a requisition for barrels of whiskey rather than molasses. Carson may not have found it funny. He was a dedicated officer with no time for shenanigans. He spent his career reporting to men who were his inferiors but he was loyal to them all. His instinct about relations with these tribes were more astute than his superiors and the tribes suffered as a result of the wrong people being in charge. If anything it made me want to read a book about the Navajo wind talkers of World War II.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8978623549243988764" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

